I am dedicating this artwork to my Ukrainian sisters and brothers, the fearless warriors, the courageous heroes and heroines on the battle front, which our nation is proud of and praying for every day. 

This drawing is about the pain, tears, unnecessary losses and senseless destruction my homeland has endured this far through the criminal act of aggression. 

Let’s stand firmly with the brave people of Ukraine in this time of crisis. 

Slava Ukraini! Glory to Ukraine!🇺🇦

For the last 8 days of Chanukah, we’ve been celebrating the overcoming of odds and gave thanks for miracles large and small. 

We often feel that we have a limited supply of “light” - energy, joy, love... Yet all we have to do is tap into it.

May this light cast out the darkness that we still see today in the world, and may the dedication to never give up on noble causes, no matter the odds, always prevail. 

Wishing you all a Happy Chanukah, and many blessings for the year ahead! 🕎🤗🍩😘

✨APPRECIATION POST✨
In the past year we have all broken down barriers and overcame (or learned) through the obstacles surrounded by our work, family and friendships.

It has been a great year for me as a graphic designer. 

When many were closing doors during Covid, I decided to open mine and start my own design company @design_hive_media.

Shout-out to everyone that has contributed to my growth in the world of art: Graphic design, Digital illustrations & Painting. I am grateful to my clients, friends and family for challenging me to be a better artist and rediscovering my passion for art in the process! ❤️

Now is the time to be and do better. 

Cheers to 2023 and to becoming the best possible version of ourselves in every way. 😎☑️ 

Happy New Year, everyone! 🤩🥂🤗
.
💇🏻‍♀️& 💄by the incredible @lifewith.shiva

Make your goals a priority! 💯
Oftentimes, the steps we plan on taking to lead us closer towards our goals are tough or even might seem impossible at first glance. 
⁣
And most of the time we have to sacrifice short term happiness to truly reap the reward of the long term success. 
⁣
Ultimately, your results are determined by your daily actions. ⁣
⁣
We get out what we put in. ⁣
⁣
Take a moment to reflect on your goals and whether you’re happy with how you’re spending your time and decide whether you could be putting more time and energy towards that goal. ⁣

This sort of practice helps me not just with training but also in my design work & life endeavours in general! 🤩

If you are serious about your health and fitness and ready to level up, I welcome you to schedule your fitness consultation and training sessions with me to embark on your personal fitness journey! 😎💪

I can’t think of anything more ill-timed and cold-hearted than what transpired in the last few days..The unprecedented viciousness coming from Hamas aimed at innocent families and children.

Hamas started a war against Israel, resulting in the worst massacre of innocent civilians in Israel's history. 

I am uncertain as to which saddens and frightens me more: seeing women being taken and raped, innocent people taken hostage or being slaughtered while being watched by the terrorists laughing and singing with joy, kids beheaded, dogs being shot..Or the people who so desperately support them for all their actions..

Everyone—no matter your views on politics—should condemn those brutal acts of violence.

Israel has been there since the dawn of times. 

If you look back at the history, the Jewish people had survived Pharaoh, Haman, Antiochus, Titus, Hitler and WE WILL survive Hamas and Hezbollah. 

Israel isn’t going anywhere. The Jewish state and the Jewish people are here to stay. 

Am Israel Chai עם ישראל חי 🇮🇱💪
.
